The State Government has issued guidelines for selection of beneficiaries for pension to old-aged artistes. The amount of monthly pension was hiked by the State Government in September 2014 from Rs. 500 to Rs. 1,500. Director, Language and Culture, said in an official press release on Friday that the selection of beneficiaries would take place in two stages â€“ at district and State-level. A total of 2,048 old-aged artistes are already getting the pension and the selection of new beneficiaries would be done to sanction pensions to 1,200 more eligible artistes additionally.